# Touch Detection System using TTP223

## ğŸ“– Overview
This project demonstrates how to interface the **TTP223 capacitive touch sensor** with an Arduino board.
The system reads digital input from the sensor and displays structured output on the **Serial Monitor**.

---

## ğŸ› ï¸ Hardware Requirements
- Arduino board (Uno, Nano, or compatible)
- TTP223 capacitive touch sensor
- Jumper wires
- USB cable for programming and power

---

## âš™ï¸ Circuit Connections
| Arduino Pin | TTP223 Pin |
|-------------|------------|
| **D2**      | OUT        |
| **5V**      | VCC        |
| **GND**     | GND        |

